    <h2><span style="color: #004b87;">Objective</span></h2>
    <p>In this lab, you will transition your Romi from a remotely controlled robot to an autonomous robot. You will use the RPLidar A1 to detect obstacles, process the incoming LiDAR data, and implement a simple reactive control loop that allows the robot to avoid walls and objects.</p>
    <p>The final behavior will be similar to a basic robotic vacuum. The robot will drive forward when the path is clear, stop when an obstacle is detected in front of it, turn in place, and then resume driving once the path is clear again.</p>
